sunta, giving readers fascinating and sometimes troubling glimpses of life among Cuzco's urban poor, with reflections on rural village life, factory work, haciendas, indigenous religion, and marriage and family relationships.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aPoorzPeruzCuzcovBiography. 0aQuechua IndiansvBiography. 0aQuechua IndiansxSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh1 aEscalante Gutierrez, Carmen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEscalante Gutiérrez, Carmen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEscobar, Gabriela Martínez.1 aGelles, Paul H.1 aGelles, Paul H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartinez Escobar, Gabriela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNishiyama, Eulogio.1 aValderrama Fernandez, Ricardo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aValderrama Fernández, Ricardo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292748354423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292748354/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK